programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Deconstructing Mike

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Ladder
programme.desc: A large family in Shrewsbury, MA, has been living with a spirit for the last 40 years. To most of the siblings, the entity is menacing and evil, but Sandy seems to have a different connection.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Devil in Syracuse
programme.desc: The clients are new, but the spirit is all too familiar as Ryan Buell prepares himself to battle the taunting demon that has been following him.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dead Legends
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/Medium Chip Coffey investigate the famed Hotel Conneaut in northern Pennsylvania. Heavy doors opening on their own, sightings of a boy, a bride and a menacing butcher have the hotel's staff on edge.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Shadow Caster
programme.desc: PRS investigates an Alabama home where clients, Georgiana and her two daughters, are so terrified, they moved out after only 18 months. They have seen shadow figures, been touched and have a recorded EVP stating, "Look at me, get out of here."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Satan's Soldier
programme.desc: Mark and Kim can't sleep through the racket caused by unseen forces in their central Indiana home. When PRS and Psychic/Medium Michelle Belanger discover what appears to be blood in the basement, they investigate a history of violence in the home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Woman in the Window
programme.desc: Ryan and his team lend paranormal assistance to a family who lives in a historic home that was once a part of the Underground Railroad. Does the answer to their haunting lie in the mysterious tunnels beneath the house?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hide and Seek
programme.desc: Hillary and her nine-year-old son Hunter are being harassed by a shadow presence in their Victorian home in Newburgh, Indiana. Trap doors in the basement reveal artifacts from a bygone era, and the clients have recorded persistent strange noises.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Pet Cemetery
programme.desc: Ryan and his team investigate the bizarre haunting of a woman and her dog in Waterboro, Maine. The Labrador was chewing at her own fur and standing on guard on the bed, growling at unseen figures.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hall I' th' Wood
programme.desc: The team investigates Hall I' th' Wood that boasts myriad tales of hauntings. Visitors report sightings of a peculiar white mist, a grey lady, strange lights and footsteps made by unseen feet.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Exeter Old Courts
programme.desc: The team investigates the Exeter Old Courts in Devon, where many people have been sentenced to death. The last hanging for witchcraft took place here during the infamous Bideford witch trial.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Niddry Street Vaults
programme.desc: The team investigates the Niddry Street Vaults where witches, poltergeists and an evil misogynist await. The damp and dirty walls hold a myriad supernatural occurrences that defy explanation.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Jedburgh Castle
programme.desc: The team investigates Jedburgh Castle, an Industrial Revolution-era prison at the center of many stories of strange sightings, odd happenings and reports of phantom pipe music heard at night.

programme.title: Most Haunted: S.S. Great Britain
programme.desc: The team explores the S.S. Great Britain, the largest and strongest ship ever built. Stories of hauntings and the chance to be the first to carry out a paranormal investigation here spur the crew on.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Newton House
programme.desc: Yvette and the "Most Haunted" team travel deep into the heart of darkest Wales to Newton House where stories of strangulation, suicide and deadly revenge await.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Madame Tussauds
programme.desc: London is the destination for Yvette and the "Most Haunted" team, where fear, dread and eerie doppelgangers await in the most famous tourist attraction in the world.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Wookey Hole
programme.desc: The team visits Wookey Hole, where legend has it a witch once turned to stone. Clashing cymbals and ancient pagan rituals await as the team explores spectacular caves said to lead to the underworld.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Banker and The Bum
programme.desc: A greedy banker and a good-hearted bum switch places. The bum dies, but the banker is now infused with love and generosity.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Brightest Star
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark meet a child star whose fame is spoiling her rotten, destroying her family and taking away her childhood.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Investment In Caring
programme.desc: Jonathan encourages residents in a neighborhood to unite against a cold-hearted developer.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Right Thing
programme.desc: Jonathan inspires a young man to help the grandfather who has recently been placed in a nursing home.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 1
programme.desc: Lizzy MacGill is a horse trainer's young daughter who elopes with Garth Armstrong, a privileged man.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark try to help Lizzie. The new bride has cancer and she is pregnant.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song for Jason - Part 1
programme.desc: Mark and Jonathan become counselors at a camp for children with cancer.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Super-Mom, Super Tired
programme.desc: Three kids in three years, a career, and years of sun worshiping has left this super-mom looking less than super. After hi-tech procedures at the dermatologist, a Pilates session, new outfit and makeup, will this mom look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Estelle Bell
programme.desc: Estelle Bell is desperately in need of a confidence shake up. Can Fiona McDonald and her team of experts convince Estelle she's still young at heart and make her look 10 Years Younger in just 10 days?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Diana Turner
programme.desc: Working with men all day, Diana Turner feels more like one of the lads than one of the ladies. It's up to Fiona McDonald and the team of experts to banish Diana's tom-boy look and make her appear 10 Years Younger in just 10 days.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hip Hop Momma
programme.desc: Jessika is a working mother of two young children who's responsibilities of motherhood has left her with little time and energy for her appearance. Now she wishes she could regain some of that old sexy feeling while being a mom.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Scrubs No More
programme.desc: Darcey spends her days caring for three kids and her nights working as a nurse, with no time left for herself. Experts perform the latest procedures in dermatology and dentistry, and the glam squad takes her from scrubs to sass.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Changing For The Better
programme.desc: After Lasik to get rid of her glasses and some dermatology to give her skin a more youthful appearance, Laura gets overhauled by the Glam Squad. Now, Laura can see without her coke bottle glasses, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Crystal Clear
programme.desc: Crystal has been taking care of other people since she was eight years old; after her mother had a stroke, she cared for her younger brother. Crystal needs to focus on herself for a change. Experts do what it takes to reclaim her youthful appearance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Teacher Learns A Lesson
programme.desc: After a major dental overhaul and LASIK to get rid of her glasses, Patricia is ready for a pop quiz in Beauty 101 from the Glam Squad. Now Patricia can spot the slackers in the back of her classroom, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: First Class Male
programme.desc: Daryl is a postal worker who commutes nearly 2 hours each way to work. This hard working father doesn't have time to get haircuts, shave or shop for clothes. Now its time for Daryl to take care of himself.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Serving Up a New Look
programme.desc: Dirk has been a busy restaurant owner for as long as he can remember. Long hours running three different establishments kept him from ever having time to take care of himself. Now, he's retired and ready to get on with life, but can't seem to get a date.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Back to Hog Heaven
programme.desc: Once comfortable on the back of her husband's Harley, this biker babe has lost all confidence in her looks. Now her aging appearance is keeping her from the fun things in life – all that used to make her happy.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Shopping For a New Look
programme.desc: Karyn is a busy working wife and mother of three, whose current frumpy appearance isn't matching the way she feels inside. It's the goal of our experts to fashion Karyn a more youthful, trendsetting look as we try make her look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 35 year old Richard Power was living life to the limits – and it showed. A year later, we recap Richard's rocky relationship with our femme fatale of flair – and see whether a catch-up with Nicky will set things straight.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Bringing Out The Spunk
programme.desc: Cat has a dream job working with rock stars and she lost 125 pounds with diet and exercise. She's worked hard to get where she is, but its left her looking more 30-something than 20-something. Our team is ready to jam on her makeover and do what it takes.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rapunzel, Rapunzel, We Must Cut Your Hair!
programme.desc: Dorothy is a single mother of two whose life changed recently when her long time employer closed its doors. Dorothy knows that years of smoking and the stress of raising her sons alone has aged her.
programme.sub-title: Rapunzel, Rapunzel, We Must Cut Your Hair!

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Danny is delighted to have his veterinary license back again and being back at work is helping to distract him from the impending anniversary of Sarah's death.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Du Plessis is restless after his heart surgery but the family insist he needs to relax. Meanwhile Danny and Alice are happy to have closed down a zoo down that has been mistreating animals.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: While on honeymoon in London, Alice discovers that Danny has some final business to do before they can return home to Africa. He's reluctantly arranged to meet his estranged father, Robert, who has recently got back in touch.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny is throwing himself into his work after the death of his father, and has applied for the role of State Vet. However, Danny's attempts to involve Thabo in the first phase of the Lion Breeding Project lead to Du Plessis feeling like an outsider.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: It is Danny's first day as State Vet and when he helps rescue some smuggled animals he feels he's making a difference. However, he discovers the role isn't going to be all plain sailing.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny's first big project as State Vet is a major animal translocation, and he is desperate to impress. Meanwhile, whilst Alice is out in the bush treating an injured zebra, she is stalked by lions. She makes it back to her jeep in time but is shaken up.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Alice is still suffering from a loss of nerve after her close shave with the lions and so Danny tries to help her overcome her problems – the Leopard's Den lions have produced their first cub and he needs Alice back in the saddle.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: In his role as State Vet, Danny works with wealthy conservationist, Anton Ziegler, to catch a group of leopard hunters. Ziegler is also buying a tiger from Vanessa, who struggling with her finances, desperately needs the money to ensure Mara's future.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: The embassy is called to a young couple in crisis. Their 7 month-old baby girl, Laney, has died from a virus and they need to get her home to Australia. But can they get baby Laney on the plane?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: The embassy is on high alert after a wealthy Australian banker goes missing. Is he alive? Holed up in a bar somewhere? Or does he not want to be found?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: Jarryd's been busted for drugs in a country where they still have the death penalty. And now he plans to double-cross the Thai authorities and escape to Singapore with his pregnant girlfriend.

programme.title: Addicted to Boob Jobs
programme.desc: Through the eyes of 26-year-old fashion journalist Louise Roe, we look at six women who are not satisfied with having just one boob job but who are choosing to return to the operating table.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save two teenage girls fighting for their lives after their car crashed and rolled the Waiwera Hill.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Professional scuba diver Brian Green has been found floating and not breathing, and is on a boat near the Noises, a group of islands in the Hauraki Gulf. The team has to move fast.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: On Great Mercury Island near Coromandel, a scuba diver has surfaced unconscious without a pulse. Without Rescue 1 he may soon be dead.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team respond to a call out where an elderly couple in their 60s are in a critical condition after a head on collision.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: A truck driver who had one leg amputated 40 years ago, has crashed his truck and crushed his remaining leg. If Rescue 1 can't get him to hospital in time, he will bleed to death.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: A car crashes another car at a country intersection. It's situation critical with four people trapped. It turns out someone was running from the police – and he was on drugs.

programme.title: Made In: Porsche Panamera
programme.desc: In 2004 Porsche decided to build the all-new Carrera GT in Leipzig, which is seen as a knightly accolade for the production site. However, the biggest challenge arose, when Porsche decided to produce a four-door sedan in parallel to the Cayenne.

programme.title: Made In: Volkswagen Phaeton
programme.desc: 2001 saw the new beginning of new chapter for Volkswagen. After getting famous for everyday cars such as the Beetle and Golf, the German car manufacturer wanted to be involved in the production of luxury vehicles, too.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Motorcycle Production
programme.desc: Sheer Driving Pleasure: That’s how BMW advertises not only its cars, but its motorcycles as well. For more than 40 years, these 2-wheelers have stood for maximum comfort, quality, and safety.

programme.title: Made In: AMG
programme.desc: AMG - Three letters that fascinate car fans all over the world. They are an abbreviation for a company, which meets the highest automotive requirements. They stand for emotion, power and unique cars.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Sustainability
programme.desc: By putting many thoughts into the cutting process of raw materials, BMW reduces the amount of waste drastically. Most of the 600 tons of sheet metal that are produced by BMW’s pressing plant ends up in the final cars, while only 10 kg go to waste.

programme.title: Made In: 125 Years of Mercedes-Benz
programme.desc: Mercedes-Benz celebrates 125 years of automotive history. 1926 the brand name arises as a result of the consolidation of Mercedes, the Daimler Motor Company and Benz by Benz & Co.

programme.title: Made In: Kiekert
programme.desc: Kiekert from North Rhine-Westphalia in Germany is a supplier for many different locking systems and the market leader in side door locks. Customers from all over the world buy door locks from Kiekert.

programme.title: Made In: Audi R8 GT
programme.desc: By now, Audi has sold more than 16,000 sports cars around the world. In 2010 they upped the stakes even more and introduced the Audi R8 GT. The high performance sports car is limited on 333 units.

programme.title: Made In: Alpina
programme.desc: Alpina symbolizes modern engineering, high precision in engine design and finest materials. The green and blue cachet has guaranteed highest quality for more than 40 years. Alpina specializes in premium BMW tuning and successful motorsports.

programme.title: Made In: Self-Driving Cars
programme.desc: Autonomous driving, which means that the car operates independently, sounds like a crazy idea, but is seen as the future of mobility. Steps towards this reality are already done thanks to the progress made in Germany.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Series 5 GT, Part 1
programme.desc: In 2003 the automotive industry was booming like never before and the law of supply and the supply-demand system works perfectly. So many manufacturers decided to develop new cars.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Series 5 GT, Part 2
programme.desc: The automotive industry is a brutal business and the genesis of new models is a jealousy kept secret. However, Made In was able to document the production history of a BMW model.

programme.title: Made In: Volkner Mobile
programme.desc: With its length of up to 12 meters and its weight of 18 tons, the Performance by Volkner is the most extraordinary luxury motor home from Germany and one of the most exclusive carvans in the world.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Adventure bike for globetrotters / Bike Tour through Scotland
programme.desc: The Honda Africa Twin is back. From 1988 to 2004, it was the ultimate bike for enduro fans. The model of the modern era is hunting down the competition from BMW and KTM. We investigate the secret of its success.
programme.sub-title: Adventure bike for globetrotters / Bike Tour through Scotland

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW
programme.desc: An incredible 215 hp with a total weight of only 149 kilos: the BMW HP4 RACE is a true racing bike. The model is limited and highly sought-after.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: One Taelon Avenue
programme.desc: Joshua Doors is running his own technology development company and Renee goes undercover to find out what is going on. An artificial intelligence program of the Taelons that controls human minds seems to be acting on its own.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Abduction
programme.desc: A volunteer who was working to interpret an ancient message from Ma'el assaults Da'an and escapes through a portal. Sandoval helps Da'an avoid interrogation from Zo'or while they try to locate her.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Arrival
programme.desc: A Taelon shuttle is shot down over Antarctica. There are Jiridians aboard, but two of the passengers escape. When Augur discovers Lili's blood on the ship, he is convinced that she is not dead.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Forge of Creation

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: First Breath
programme.desc: A college friend of Renee's resurfaces and leads them on an investigation of the link between the Taelons and a biomedical facility's cloning operation.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Sins of the Father
programme.desc: A Senator's daughter is found to have kryss in her system. Liam and Renee suspect the Taelons lied about synthesizing it and there is a new location for production. They believe Federov is involved. Da'an is addicted to kryss.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Limbo

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Motherlode
programme.desc: Augur is caught and placed in a special prison where he is placed in a sensory deprivation chamber. An amoralist gets him out and wants Augur to help him steal the gold Zo'or has on the mothership. When Liam learns of what happened he tries to find Augur.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Take No Prisoners
programme.desc: The ANA negotiate amnesty for all resistance members, Liam tries to convince resistance member Halley Simmons to take the offer. Sandoval uses parasites to make volunteers do suicide missions against the resistance.
